## Tool Usage Examples

### jira_search

Parameter: `search_term` - text searched in issue titles.

### jira_get_issue

Parameter: `issue_key` - Jira issue key.

Returns: Summary, Status, Assignee, AssigneeAccountId, Reporter, ReporterAccountId, Priority, Created, Updated, Description, Comments (with authorAccountId).

### jira_add_comment

Parameters: `issue_key`, `body` (Jira wiki markup), optionally `reply_to_comment_id`.

### jira_transition_issue

Parameters: `issue_key`, `status_name` (target status name).

### jira_assign_issue

Parameters: `issue_key`, `assignee`. Special values: `"reporter"`, `"unassigned"`, or an accountId.

### email_send

Parameters: `user`, `to`, `subject`, `body`. Recipients validated by whitelist (toolbox configuration).

### schedule_followup

Schedules a follow-up task for a specific time. Use when you need to check something later.

Parameters:
- `user` - Your email from SOUL.md
- `issue_key` - Jira issue key for the follow-up
- `scheduled_at` - Date and time in ISO 8601 format (e.g. `"2026-02-24T16:30:00"`)
- `instructions` - Detailed instructions for what to do when the time comes (10-2000 characters)

